    "content": "<h2>Fake Reviews Are a Real Problem</h2><p>Whether it is a disgruntled ex-employee, a competitor, or spam â€” fake Google reviews can tank your rating and cost you customers. The good news: Google does remove fake reviews if you know how to report them.</p><h2>Step 1: Identify the Fake Review</h2><p>Before reporting, make sure it is actually fake:</p><ul><li>The reviewer has never been a customer (check your records)</li><li>The review describes a product or service you do not offer</li><li>The reviewer profile is brand new with only 1 review</li><li>Multiple 1-star reviews appeared on the same day</li><li>The review is copied from another business listing</li><li>It contains irrelevant content or spam links</li></ul><h2>Step 2: Flag the Review from Google Maps</h2><ol><li>Open Google Maps and find your business</li><li>Click on the review you want to report</li><li>Click the three-dot menu (â‹®) next to the review</li><li>Select <strong>\"Flag as inappropriate\"</strong></li><li>Choose the reason that best applies</li><li>Submit the report</li></ol><p>Google typically reviews flagged content within 3-5 business days.</p><h2>Step 3: Report Through Google Business Profile</h2><ol><li>Go to <a href=\"https://business.google.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">business.google.com</a></li><li>Select your business</li><li>Go to <strong>Reviews</strong></li><li>Find the review and click the three-dot menu</li><li>Select <strong>\"Report review\"</strong></li><li>Fill out the report form with specific details</li></ol><h2>Step 4: Use the Google Reviews Removal Tool</h2><p>If previous steps do not work after a week:</p><ol><li>Go to <a href=\"https://support.google.com/business/answer/4596773\" rel=\"nofollow\">Google Business Review Management Support</a></li><li>Select your business and the specific review</li><li>Provide evidence the review violates Google policies</li></ol><h2>Step 5: Respond Publicly While Waiting</h2><p>Post a professional response so other customers see you take reviews seriously:</p><blockquote>We do not have any record of this visit in our system. We take all feedback seriously. If you have visited us, please contact us at [email/phone].</blockquote><h2>What Google Will and Will Not Remove</h2><p><strong>Google WILL remove:</strong></p><ul><li>Spam or fake content</li><li>Off-topic reviews (not about customer experience)</li><li>Restricted content (illegal, explicit)</li><li>Conflict of interest (competitors, ex-employees)</li><li>Impersonation</li></ul><p><strong>Google will NOT remove:</strong></p><ul><li>Reviews you disagree with</li><li>Low ratings without text</li><li>Honest negative experiences</li><li>Reviews from dissatisfied real customers</li></ul><h2>How Long Does Removal Take?</h2><ul><li><strong>Flag from Maps:</strong> 3-14 days</li><li><strong>Report from Business Profile:</strong> 3-7 days</li><li><strong>Removal tool:</strong> 5-14 days</li><li><strong>Legal removal:</strong> 30+ days</li></ul><h2>Prevention Is Better Than Removal</h2><p>The best defense against fake reviews is a strong volume of real, positive reviews. A single fake 1-star barely dents a business with 100+ genuine reviews.</p><ul><li>Ask every happy customer for a review</li><li>Use QR codes at your counter and on receipts</li><li>Send SMS/email follow-ups after service</li><li>Use smart review gating to catch unhappy customers privately</li></ul><div class=\"blog-cta\"><h3>Build a wall of real reviews</h3><p>ReviewFlow helps you collect genuine 5-star reviews consistently, making fake reviews irrelevant.</p><a href=\"/signup\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Start Collecting Real Reviews â€” Free</a></div>"
